STATE EX REL. HOBART
v.
INDUS. COMM. 2018-1241 Supreme Court of Ohio. October 25, 2018

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

Pursuant to R.C. 2710.06(B)(1), the court has been notified that the parties in this case have reached a settlement. The case is returned to the regular docket under S.Ct.Prac.R. 19.01. Within 60 days, appellant shall file an application for dismissal or file a merit brief in accordance with Supreme Court Rules of Practice. This case will be dismissed for want of prosecution if an application for dismissal or merit brief is not filed within 60 days.
